    "media_with_text_wCfREr": {
      "type": "media-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "image_kt4YnY": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify:\/\/shop_images\/green_cassette_yellow_background.jpg",
            "media_width": 50,
            "media_position": "end",
            "text_position": "place-self-center text-center",
            "icon": "none",
            "icon_width": 48,
            "subheading": "",
            "title": "The birth of an idea...",
            "content": "<p>The <a href=\"https:\/\/voxblock.co.uk\/blogs\/news\/the-birth-of-an-idea\" title=\"The birth of an idea...\">idea for Voxblock began<\/a> when we came across some old cassettes and played them for our daughter. She loved listening to them, but struggled to insert the tapes and press the buttons by herself.<\/p><p>And since cassettes are not widely produced anymore, it was difficult to find new stories for her to listen to. We experimented with using a tablet, but that came with its own set of challenges. We needed to find a new way for her to listen to her favourite stories, and it needed to be screen free.<\/p>",
            "link_text": "",
            "link_url": "",
            "background": "#ffffff",
            "background_gradient": "",
            "text_color": "#565656",
            "text_gradient": "",
            "button_background": "",
            "button_text_color": ""
          }
        },
        "image_pqe6Qf": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify:\/\/shop_images\/lightbulb.jpg",
            "media_width": 50,
            "media_position": "start",
            "text_position": "place-self-center text-center",
            "icon": "none",
            "icon_width": 48,
            "subheading": "",
            "title": "What now?",
            "content": "<p>We experimented with several available audio players but they never quite delivered on our requirements. We wanted a player that was simple for children to use independently, and tangible books that they could bond with. Plus, we wanted a device that could survive the bumps and bangs of everyday use; it needed to be built to last.<\/p>",
            "link_text": "",
            "link_url": "",
            "background": "#ffffff",
            "background_gradient": "",
            "text_color": "#565656",
            "text_gradient": "",
            "button_background": "",
            "button_text_color": ""
          }
        },
        "image_arXR9d": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify:\/\/shop_images\/two-children-swap-audiobooks.jpg",
            "media_width": 50,
            "media_position": "end",
            "text_position": "place-self-center text-center",
            "icon": "none",
            "icon_width": 48,
            "subheading": "",
            "title": "Enter Voxblock",
            "content": "<p>A few weeks of tinkering in the garage later, and the first Voxblock prototype was born. It ticked all our boxes, and our daughter loved using it too.<\/p><p>We shared this prototype with family and friends, whose enthusiasm confirmed there was a need for a simple, screen free audiobook player.<\/p>",
            "link_text": "",
            "link_url": "",
            "background": "#ffffff",
            "background_gradient": "",
            "text_color": "#565656",
            "text_gradient": "",
            "button_background": "",
            "button_text_color": ""
          }
        }
      },
